Paper: hep-th/9611135

Date: 1996-11-18

Title: D-branes in the light-cone gauge and broken symmetries

Authors: Michael Gutperle (DAMTP, University of Cambridge, UK)

Comments: 8 pages, Latex, uses sprocl.sty, Contribution to the workshop "Gauge

Theories, Applied Supersymmetry and Quantum Gravity", London, ImperialCollege, July 1996Boundary states for D-branes are constructed using the light cone gauge. TheD-brane breaks half the spacetime supersymmetry giving rise to fermionic zeromodes living on the brane. The nonlinear realization of the brokensupersymmetry on the open string degrees of freedom is analysed and theinfluence of boundary terms coming from closed string vertex operators isdiscussed.